Steps:
1. rvm use 2.4.1 (ruby version)
2. rvm gemset create bookstore
3. rvm gemset use bookstore
4. gem install rails -v '4.2.8'
5. rails new bookstore mysql2
6. bundle install
7. gem install therubyracer
8. rake db:create
9. rails s
10. mysql -u root -p (to check the database environment)
11. rails g scaffold user name:string city:string mobile:integer
12. rake db:migrate
13. start server
